.TH DABCTL 1 "2026-04-07" "0.6.0" "DAB Radio Tools"
.SH NAME
dabctl \- receive DAB radio via RTL-SDR and decode to PCM audio
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dabctl iq2pcm
.RB [ \-C
.IR channel ]
.RB [ \-G
.IR gain ]
.RB [ \-p
.IR ppm ]
.RB [ \-Q ]
.RB [ \-d
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-D
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-s
.IR sid ]
.RB [ \-l
.IR label ]
.RB [ \-1 ]
.RB [ \-F ]
.RB [ \-S
.IR dir ]
.RB [ \-\-slide\-base64 ]
.RB [ \-\-silent ]
.RB [ \-\-device\-index
.IR n ]
.PP
.B dabctl iq2eti
.RB [ \-C
.IR channel ]
.RB [ \-G
.IR gain ]
.RB [ \-p
.IR ppm ]
.RB [ \-Q ]
.RB [ \-d
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-D
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-O
.IR file ]
.RB [ \-t
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-S ]
.RB [ \-\-device\-index
.IR n ]
.PP
.B eti\-rtlsdr\-rust eti2pcm
.RB [ \-s
.IR sid ]
.RB [ \-l
.IR label ]
.RB [ \-1 ]
.RB [ \-p ]
.RB [ \-F ]
.RB [ \-S
.IR dir ]
.RB [ \-\-slide\-base64 ]
.RI [ file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dabctl
provides three subcommands for DAB (Digital Audio Broadcasting) processing:
.SS iq2pcm
Receives DAB signals from an RTL-SDR dongle, demodulates the OFDM signal,
decodes the FIC (Fast Information Channel) and the selected audio service,
and writes PCM audio directly to stdout.
This is a single\-process pipeline: no ETI serialisation takes place,
reducing latency and memory usage compared to the
.I iq2eti | eti2pcm
pipeline.
.SS iq2eti
Receives DAB signals from an RTL-SDR dongle, demodulates the OFDM signal,
decodes the FIC (Fast Information Channel), and outputs ETI-NI frames
(6144 bytes each) on stdout or to a file.
This is a faithful port of
.I eti\-cmdline
(C++) to Rust.
.SS eti2pcm
Reads ETI frames from stdin or a file, selects an audio service (DAB or DAB+),
decodes it to PCM audio written to stdout. Optionally outputs DAB metadata
(ensemble info, service info, Dynamic Label) as JSON on file descriptor 3.
This is a port of
.I dablin
(C++) to Rust.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS iq2pcm options
All options from both
.B iq2eti
and
.B eti2pcm
are available in a single invocation.
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-channel " " \fIchannel\fR
DAB channel to tune to (e.g., 5A, 6C, 11C).
Default:
.BR 11C .
.TP
.BR \-G ", " \-\-gain " " \fIpercent\fR
Tuner gain as a percentage from 0 to 100.
Default:
.BR 50 .
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-ppm " " \fIppm\fR
Frequency correction in parts per million.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.TP
.BR \-Q ", " \-\-autogain
Enable automatic gain control (AGC). Overrides
.BR \-G .
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-sync\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout for time synchronization.
Default:
.BR 5 .
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-detect\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout for ensemble detection.
Default:
.BR 10 .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-sid " " \fIsid\fR
Service ID in hexadecimal (e.g., 0xF2F8). Selects the audio service to decode.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-label " " \fIlabel\fR
Select service by label name.
.TP
.BR \-1 ", " \-\-first
Play the first audio service found in the ensemble.
.TP
.BR \-F ", " \-\-disable\-dyn\-fic
Disable dynamic FIC messages on stderr.
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-slide\-dir " " \fIdir\fR
Save slideshow images to the specified directory.
.TP
.BR \-\-slide\-base64
Output slideshow images as base64\-encoded JSON on file descriptor 3.
.TP
.BR \-\-silent
Suppress all log output on stderr.
.TP
.BI \-\-device\-index " n"
RTL-SDR device index.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.SS iq2eti options
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-channel " " \fIchannel\fR
DAB channel to tune to. Examples: 5A, 6C, 11C, 12C.
Band III channels (5A\-13F, 174\-240 MHz) and L-Band channels (LA\-LP, 1452\-1478 MHz) are supported.
Default:
.BR 11C .
.TP
.BR \-G ", " \-\-gain " " \fIpercent\fR
Tuner gain as a percentage from 0 to 100.
Default:
.BR 50 .
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-ppm " " \fIppm\fR
Frequency correction in parts per million.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.TP
.BR \-Q ", " \-\-autogain
Enable automatic gain control (AGC). Overrides
.BR \-G .
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-sync\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout for time synchronization (null symbol detection).
Default:
.BR 5 .
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-detect\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout for ensemble detection (FIC decoding).
Default:
.BR 10 .
.TP
.BR \-O ", " \-\-output " " \fIfile\fR
Output file path. Use
.B \-
for stdout.
Default: stdout.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-record\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Recording duration.
.B \-1
means indefinite.
Default:
.BR \-1 .
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-silent
Suppress status messages on stderr.
.TP
.BI \-\-device\-index " n"
RTL-SDR device index.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.SS eti2pcm options
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-sid " " \fIsid\fR
Service ID in hexadecimal (e.g., 0xF2F8 or F2F8). Selects the audio service to decode.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-label " " \fIlabel\fR
Select service by label name (case-sensitive match).
.TP
.BR \-1 ", " \-\-first
Play the first audio service found in the ensemble.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-pcm
Enable PCM output on stdout. Signed 16-bit little-endian, stereo.
Sample rate is typically 48000 Hz (or 32000 Hz for some DAB+ services).
.TP
.BR \-F ", " \-\-disable\-dyn\-fic
Disable dynamic FIC messages on stderr.
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-slide\-dir " " \fIdir\fR
Save slideshow images (JPEG/PNG) to the specified directory.
The directory is created automatically if it does not exist.
Files are named using the MOT ContentName field or a default name.
.TP
.BR \-\-slide\-base64
Output slideshow images as base64-encoded JSON on file descriptor 3.
Each slide is written as a JSON object (see
.B JSON METADATA
below).
.TP
.I file
ETI input file. If omitted, reads from stdin.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal termination (Ctrl-C or record time reached).
.TP
.B 1
No DAB signal found within sync timeout.
.TP
.B 3
RTL-SDR device initialization failed.
.TP
.B 4
Invalid channel name.
.TP
.B 5
Failed to start RTL-SDR reader.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B Direct RTL-SDR to PCM (single process):
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2pcm \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Direct with JSON metadata on fd 3:
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2pcm \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \-\-slide\-base64 3>meta.json \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Direct, play first service with AGC:
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2pcm \-C 11C \-Q \-1 | aplay \-f S16_LE \-r 48000 \-c 2
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Full pipeline \(em RTL-SDR to audio:
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2eti \-S \-C 6C \-G 20 \\
  | dabctl eti2pcm \-F \-s 0xF2F8 \-p \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Pipeline with JSON metadata on fd 3:
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2eti \-S \-C 6C \-G 20 \\
  | dabctl eti2pcm \-F \-s 0xF2F8 \-p 3>metadata.json \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Save ETI to a file:
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2eti \-C 6C \-G 20 \-O capture.eti
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Decode an ETI file to PCM:
.RS
.nf
dabctl eti2pcm \-s 0xF2F8 \-p capture.eti > output.raw
ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 output.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Convert to WAV (iq2pcm):
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2pcm \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \\
  | sox \-t raw \-r 48000 \-b 16 \-c 2 \-e signed\-integer \-L \- output.wav
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Record 60 seconds of ETI:
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2eti \-C 5A \-G 70 \-t 60 \-O capture.eti
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Play first service from stdin:
.RS
.nf
dabctl eti2pcm \-1 \-p < capture.eti | aplay \-f S16_LE \-r 48000 \-c 2
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Save slideshow images:
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2pcm \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \-S /tmp/slides \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Pipe to dablin (compatibility):
.RS
.nf
dabctl iq2eti \-S \-C 6C \-G 20 | dablin \-s 0xF2F8
.fi
.RE
.SH ETI FORMAT
Each ETI-NI frame is exactly 6144 bytes and contains:
.TP
.B SYNC (4 bytes)
Frame synchronization word.
.TP
.B LIDATA
FIC data (96 bytes of FIB) followed by MSC subchannel data.
.TP
.B EOF (4 bytes)
CRC-16 and padding.
.TP
.B TIST (4 bytes)
Timestamp (set to 0xFFFFFFFF).
.TP
.B Padding
Remaining bytes filled with 0x55.
.PP
At 24 frames per second, the ETI bitrate is approximately 1.2 Mbit/s.
.SH JSON METADATA (eti2pcm)
When file descriptor 3 is open, the
.B eti2pcm
subcommand writes DAB metadata as JSON lines (one JSON object per line):
.PP
.B Ensemble information:
.RS
.nf
{"ensemble":{"eid":"0x1234","label":"My Ensemble"}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Selected service:
.RS
.nf
{"service":{"sid":"0xF2F8","label":"NRJ"}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Dynamic Label (DLS):
.RS
.nf
{"dl":"Now playing: Song Title - Artist"}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Slideshow (with \-\-slide\-base64):
.RS
.nf
{"slide":{"contentName":"logo.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","data":"base64..."}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Slideshow JSON is only emitted when
.B \-\-slide\-base64
is passed.
.PP
This format is compatible with
.I dablin
(gregoire fork) fd 3 output.
